; native-translation-model.form — OUR translation learning model, COMPOSED from the body's
; existing native-ML tissue, with the data kept OUTSIDE the recipe. A design + assembly cell;
; the stages below are the build, each a four-way band for its pure compute.
;
; THE ASK (Urs, 2026-06-14):
;   "A transformer is one solution; Google research showed adding diffusion can improve the
;    model ~10x; we have features no other ML runtime has — try them with auto-research and
;    auto-ml; come up with OUR OWN translation learning model, and keep the data OUTSIDE the
;    recipe."
;
; READ THE BODY FIRST — the pieces already exist; this composes them, it does not reinvent:
;   - form-native-llm.form          [INFER] the native-ML shape, and it IS "the features no
;       other runtime has": embedding = a content-addressed COORDINATE (the NodeID is the
;       embedding); attention = choice/fail/cut/stop sparse retrieval (a wrong path is O(1) to
;       abandon); `nothing` = honest abstain; layers = recipes that dedup holographically and
;       can rewrite themselves (architecture-as-data). Companion: form-native-models.form
;       proves a standard transformer runs deterministically in Form.
;   - ml-diffusion-model-flow.form  native diffusion denoising steps + embeddings + attention
;       as content-addressed Recipes — the diffusion the ask points at, already modelled here.
;   - metabolic-learning.form / geometric-learning.form  the LEARNING loop: ONE weighted
;       gather (gl-step over (i j w) edge data) carries diffusion, convolution, message-passing,
;       and embedding; the weights enter as DATA. SHIPPED (bands 4095 / 8388607).
;   - embedding-as-recipe.fk        the runnable embedding primitive — content-addressed,
;       node_eq (exact identity), embedding-distance (graded L1) — now real-float-capable
;       (the IEEE-float surface + trig + fatan2 crossed four-way).
;   - cjk-channel.fk                translation = one cell, many tongues, by content-address;
;       the meaning-as-shared-cell insight this model makes LEARNED and DYNAMIC.
;
; WHAT IS ACTUALLY MISSING (the gap this cell closes):
;   the TRANSLATION assembly of those pieces, and the data living OUTSIDE the recipe.
;   translation-learn.fk uses NONE of them — it is a hardcoded lookup, a seed lexicon.
;
; THE TRANSLATION MODEL = a composition, not a new engine:
;   encode   source faces -> content-addressed embeddings            (embedding-as-recipe)
;   denoise  start from a noised target-side embedding field; refine ALL positions in
;            parallel; each step SNAPS toward interned meaning-cells in the lattice
;            (ml-diffusion-model-flow + the discrete-attractor move content-addressing uniquely
;            allows: denoising falls toward interned cells instead of wandering a continuous
;            space — fewer steps, sharper meaning)
;   render   resolved meaning-cells -> target-tongue faces
;   learn    the weighted-gather loop trains encode/denoise/render   (metabolic / geometric)
;   gate     accept by essence/vitality/trust >= floor (translation-quality.fk), not exact
;            equality; meaning preserved == convergence to the shared cell (node_eq) — so the
;            generator and the acceptance check share ONE substrate.
;
; WEIGHTS ARE DATA CELLS, NOT RECIPES — and the recipe is the engine over them:
;   - the WEIGHTS are content-addressed DATA CELLS (the learned parameters: embeddings,
;     denoiser, render maps). They are DATA, not recipes. The RECIPE is the engine — the
;     forward/backward computation that READS the weight-cells. "Data outside the recipe"
;     means exactly this: the weights are cells, the engine is the .fk. Editing the model =
;     changing cells (learning), never typing rows of source. (The corpus — oracle output +
;     attested seeds — is likewise DATA CELLS.)
;   - BASE WEIGHTS REST IN ICE: frozen, immutable, SHARED, sharable WITHOUT SERIALIZATION.
;     Because cells are content-addressed, a model is shared by referencing its weight-cell
;     NodeIDs (like git objects by hash) — no checkpoint file format, no serialize/deserialize,
;     no byte-transfer. Two models with overlapping weights share the overlap automatically.
;   - LEARNING IS A PHASE CHANGE UNDER PRESSURE: nothing melts until there is new learning
;     pressure (a loss signal / new data). Then ONLY the affected weight-cells melt ice ->
;     water (mutable), update, and REFREEZE water -> ice as a new immutable content-addressed
;     checkpoint. Content-addressing makes the new checkpoint SHARE every unchanged weight-cell
;     with the prior — checkpoints are incremental and dedup'd for free; only the cells that
;     actually changed get new NodeIDs.
;   - HONEST SEAM: the model's COMPUTE (encode, denoise, embedding-distance, gate) is the body,
;     four-way. Sharing weights needs NO serialization (content-address by NodeID); where
;     cross-process persistence needs a host carrier, that carrier is 3-kernel (host-io
;     standing wall). Carrier persists; engine proves; content-address shares.
;
; AUTO-RESEARCH + AUTO-ML (the model improves itself, no human typing rows):
;   the ARCHITECTURE is the recipe (the engine — recipe-data); the WEIGHTS are data cells
;   (above). Auto-ml SEARCHES the architecture space: variants
;   (denoising schedule, attractor radius, embedding arity, render map) are candidate recipes;
;   champion-challenger.fk A/Bs them; model-vitality.fk + translation-quality.fk score them;
;   colearning-retire.fk promotes the winner. field-auto-research.fk frames the open questions
;   as question -> source cells -> evidence -> FMF -> answer -> residual questions.
;
; STAGES (each a four-way band for its pure compute; data external from S1):
;   S1 data-out  move the corpus out of tl-exemplars() into substrate cells; the recipe reads
;                pairs from the store. The lookup still works, but the DATA is external.
;   S2 embed     encode faces as embedding-as-recipe vectors; translate by nearest-embedding
;                retrieval (loopback-learning.fk's nearest-shape learner is the bootstrap);
;                generalises to unseen faces by similarity.
;   S3 denoise   the content-address-snapping parallel denoiser (ml-diffusion-model-flow).
;   S4 auto-ml   architecture variants searched, scored, and promoted natively.
;
; OPEN QUESTIONS (for auto-research + sister consensus — named, not yet answered):
;   - the snap rule: node_eq is exact, embedding-distance is graded — what attractor radius
;     preserves essence without collapsing distinct meanings into one cell?
;   - does the lattice's discreteness let us denoise in FEWER steps than continuous diffusion?
;   - do learned render maps (argmax over candidate faces) stay four-way deterministic?
;
; SUPERSEDES the loopback toy framing (native-translation-loopback.form); translation-learn.fk
; is honestly a SEED LEXICON, not a model.
; teaching: lc-cross-modal-unity
